&lt;p&gt;I lived full-time in a 2017 Dodge ProMaster 2500 for seven years, and I learned quickly that your power setup can make or break your day. If your battery system is unstable, everything gets harder: work, cooking, sleep, and basic comfort. I tested the Bluetti Elite 200 V2 as a practical, all-in-one option for van lifers who want less wiring complexity and more reliable daily power. This review is based on how it performs in real van conditions, not lab-only numbers.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Renogy 100W Slim Solar Panels Review: 3-Panel Stealth ProMaster Setup</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/gear/renogy-100w-slim-solar-panels-stealth-promaster-setup/</link><pubDate>Fri, 20 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/gear/renogy-100w-slim-solar-panels-stealth-promaster-setup/</guid><description>&lt;h1 class="relative group"&gt;Renogy 100W Slim Solar Panels Review: 3-Panel Stealth ProMaster Setup
